caption: Friendly staff. Great food. Try the zucchini fries!

This restaurant serves truly amazing burgers at a great price. Plus the food wasn't only great but also was served quite fast. Staff was super polite. All around great restaurant.
Fantastic food and service.  Staff are super nice and helpful.

Good burger. They do lettuce wraps if you want it instead of buns.  You walk in. Wait in line. Look at a menu then order your food. Get a number and sit down and wait.  Thing is... There were no menus to read in line. So I pulled it up on the phone. Probly missed a bunch of items doing this but whatever.  Employees were all nice.food was awesome.
The staff was really friendly and attentive. The view was nice and the good was great. Will definitely return!

Have been here a couple times now and service and food have been great.  Lunch deal of cheeseburger/fries/drink lowers cost by about $2.  Can't wait for good weather to use large patio area.  Can park on front or back side of building.  Had an issue with a Moxie gift card and manager handled it with a good customer focus.  We'll be back with our group again soon!
Black bean burger is so good! Top it with coleslaw and grilled pineapple and you've got a mouth-watering meal!
We have been thru a lot together , but thanks for feeding me
Great Menu. Food was great. Nice place to eat.

Got there about 4:15 on Superbowl Sunday,  our 1st visit so we had no idea they were closing at 5pm. Ordered 3 burgers, all med or medium well, all came out well done & not good at all, 2 star loss. For the $76 we spent for 4 sandwiches & 4 sodas we were left very unimpressed & irritated. Last star lost for employees- we overheard one tell the other "this couldn't get worse" as we ordered- what?!  Try harder Moxie Burger team in Roswell...

Thanks so much for updating your website to reflect the fact you’d be closing at 5pm on Sunday to “watch the Super Bowl”. Checked in advance online, no sign of early closing, so drove down from Canton.
Man this place is delicious!!!! Such good burgers, great beers on tap and a super kind staff that is flexible and knowledgeable!
Food arrived warm (which is good for a delivery service) but with the wrong drink. When someone orders 'coke,' it doesn't mean 'diet coke.' You lost a star for that. Sorry.
Good atmosphere, great burgers, and the staff is pretty nice. I have eaten there once but I go there often to pick up ubereats orders. They must be doing something right.
Always delicious! The black bean burger is excellent. The staff is always so nice. They never get the order wrong.
The food is always delicious and the vegan burger is the best I’ve had from a restaurant.
I had The Moxie burger, with fried pickles. Very good food, with great service. Would definitely recommend to give this place a shot whether it be a hangout with friends, or a casual date spot.
Burger was Fantastic!  Awesome sweet potato fries as well.  Patio was very busy.  Tables inside were distanced due to pandemic.  Staff was friendly and helpful!

Always a solid option. Food has always been spot on. The Heater and the Moxie Burger are both delicious. I really don’t like zucchini fries personally, but theirs are pretty damn good. Good outdoor seating options in the back patio.
I like this burguer
Great spot for Sunday Funday! Highly recommend “The Colonel” tossed in buffalo sauce on Texas toast.
Amazing burger and sweet potato fries!
Like the outdoor dinning area

This place makes a really good burger; that much is true. The fries were undercooked and had been sitting a bit. Also, this is a counter service with delivery to the table restaurant but they also ask for a tip. You aren’t supposed to tip for counter service. It felt overpriced for what I get.

Great food and service!  I was really in the mood for a burger & fries today and decided to spread my burger wings beyond my normal haunts.  This is a great place right outside of Roswell that is pretty easy to miss if you don’t know it’s there.  You order in line, take a number and go find a seat.  They have great indoor and outdoor seating areas with plenty of space between the tables.  They also have high ceilings and plenty of air flow, are following Covid19 protocols and I felt very safe dining inside.  It was also 38 degrees outside so that was a negative on the outside with a view.  The food came out very quickly and was cooked perfectly.  Our server also checked on us a couple of times and wished us a great day as we were leaving - all the things you want and need in a great burger place.
Love this place.  Amazing local burger place with great vegetarian options.
Very yummy and good times

Nice doible-patty burgers, just greasy enough to be totally satisfying, good flavor and an appropriate choixe of topping/varieties, but really not too many. Fries and sweet tato fries are crispy, fresh, handmade. Great prices on kids meal too!! Will be back.
Great place. Food was excellent.

They have some delicious sweet potato fries and that sweet chili mayo you dip them in is sent from heaven. I haven't even had a burger there! Every time I go it's for those fries 😂!! The single serving is so large I don't have room for a burger. However it's so good I never leave dissatisfied or wishing for something more. Thats saying alot because I'm a meat eater and I'm a very picky eater.
I really like the heater burger and their fries are excellent. This location has covered seating outside and has a heater.
Awesome staff and service and food!
Ok location for delicious burgers. Arrived at seven, it wasn't crowded. There was quick, helpful, and friendly service. I can see why they have a lot of good reviews.
Great burger place!  Fries are even better. Make sure to get them 50/50 and try different types.

Great environment-similar to the college bar/pub you remember from undergrad days, but suitable for all ages including families with young children. Outdoor seating with and without heaters, food is very good, vegetarian options are available for the health conscious. Nice selection of beer, ample parking behind the restaurant. Staff is exceptionally nice and accommodating. All wear masks and during time of covid social distancing is practiced in the restaurant. Convenient walk to downtown Roswell and the old mill.
Great service, great burgers and fries.
Loved it! Good food and good service. Plenty of outdoor seating.
The Turkey burger was so good. Dressed in an unexpected but delightfully delicious way. Will definitely return.
The small hamburger is just Divine.. Not too much and really just the perfect amount..
Delicious food, great service, taking ptoper Covid precautions, if you haven't been and like chicken or burgers, go. You will not regret it.
Pretty good burgers and good wine and beer selection.
Amazing place , view , people and food. Nothing more I can say perfect date location.

Meh. Just so so. Not bad.

Food was very good! Worth the stop.
Best salmon burger I've had! I was at a paint party next door and the food was delivered quickly. The food was amazing and the service was quick and pleasant. I highly recommend this burger joint!

So this place was great when it first opened...   but the past year it has dropped down from twice a week to once a month and now probably never again.    The cooks that work there can't saute onions not sure if they even know what a caramelized onion is..    They don't get the burger right on temp ever....   Then it cost 27 dollars for 2 burgers and 9ne salad.   One of the burgers is a big mushroom.   27 bucks for that ill take my money back and probably never eat there again.
Friendly staff, but the food was just ok. You also have to wait for a long time to get seated especially if you go on a weekend.

Their black bean burger was thick and not dry!   The sweet potato fries had a touch of cinnamon and sugar along with the salt.   Literally the best black bean burger and sweet potato fries I've eaten!   Plus all staff were wearing masks and were very friendly!

Love the burgers and sweet potato fries. The sauce that comes with the sweet potato fries is addictive. I've had the bleu ribbon and the moxie burgers, and both were awesome. Plenty of parking and a great location right at Roswell Mill, near Vickery Creek trails

A great burger place with quality food and great service! They have a nice deck you can sit at and enjoy your meal. The sweet potato fries were a stand-out for me - they are delish! A bit of salt and cinnamon sugar on them and made to perfection - not greasy or soggy at all! Yum!
Friendly service and delicious burgers with fresh toppings.  I'd recommend
Heater and Chicago dog are my favorites at Moxie. After a hike around the waterfall this place is an good option to get some food and a pint 🍺
I had an excellent buffalo chicken sandwich and the zucchini fries / sweet potato fries were delicious. Service was great and it was super enjoyable sitting out on the large patio. Will be returning.
Really good food! Multiple vegan/vegetarian options. Big dog-friendly deck outside. Staff is nice!
Moxie is an awesome place for burger and some fresh fries. Back patio is the place to be.
First time here but the staff welcomed me and my crew with open arms. Awesome burgers, choices of toppings, and all served hot and fresh! Highly recommended

Fantastic experience. Was my first time going there. The turkey burger with wheat bun and sweet potato fries was so fresh and tasty. The ambiance was delightful. The staff are very friendly, quick, and helpful. Definitely going back!

I had an awesome first experience! I arrived on Labor Day alone at Moxie Burger. I placed my order, I was given a number,  its self serve seating, I sat outside. The Moxie burger w side if sweet potato fries & onion rings OMG soooo delish! Prior to heading out I spent 2 hours reading reviews of various restaurants in the area because I wanted my burger to be amazing and it absolutely was just that 'Amazing!'

Amazing food.  Fresh.  Tasty.  Great social distancing practice at the establishment.

Really really good burger place with 3 locations in town.  Great food.   Very good outside seating.  Try the heater if in mood for some spicy burger.  They have lamb, turkey (and I think veg) too.  Good local place. Fries are huge !   Beer selection is small but great ones.
One of best burger joints in town.  The wait staff are very polite and attentive.   Location is great too.

Not family friendly at all. A bunch of kids work here. There are no servers and hostess to greet you when you walk in. You pour your own drinks. You seat yourself. You pay up front and they want you to sign the tip in advance. The Cadillac aka lamb burger is much smaller than the picture makes it seem and if you do a bun- less option they dont lettuce wrap it or give any additional options. Oh yeah I noticed a lot of angry old people eating here. The burger tasted good  but I spent 40 bucks and I'm still hungry. The porch has a good view but it is not toddler friendly. 👎🏼

This place is really awesome. My burger was very, very good! The bread is really good which is the key to a good burger. The outdoor patio eating area is really low key and nice. Drew who was working the front desk area was an awesome worker/waiter. He was running around doing ten things at once and was unbelievably polite. just wanted to say thank you Drew!

Probably the best burger in Roswell, and the deck has amazing views of the river and forest below, but you may spend up to 10 minutes in line waiting to get your order in, but other than that its an amazing experience
Brice was exceptional! Definitely want Team Members like her as the face of your company. Food was very good. Friendly and courteous associates

Not sure how to rate what happened today but decided to be positive.  Did takeout.  When we got home, we found out they got our order seriously wrong.  We ordered free-range burgers but instead received one grilled chicken breast burger and one turkey burger.  But they were so delicious we decided that in these crazy times, we’d forgive, forget and try again soon.  As always, the sweet potato fries are life-changing!

Lots of gluten free options to choose from. One of my favorite places to go to for a gf burger. Haven't tried much of the rest of the menu, but I would really recommend the build your own burgers (called the entrepreneur)! Make sure that the meat you choose is gf (the turkey is not, learned that the hard way) and get the gf Pure Kneads bun!! Or you can go bunless, up to you. The fries are really good, just be careful with cross contamination. But that's about it!
Excellent service and food, called in several times for to go with several burgers on the order, correct every time! Thanks Moxie burger for staying open and awesome staff!

Very disappointed the last two times we have been there. We have had take out and dine in and both times the service was poor. The staff seems overwhelmed and disorganized. The burgers were bone dry especially when you ask for medium rare burgers. They have a lot of unique options for build your own but the execution has been poor. Fried pickle chips are delicious! Hate to not support a local business but for the price and the quality there are better options locally.
My favorite casual dining spot in Roswell! Food and service are always excellent. We love to enjoy a burger and beer on the porch!

There is a reason why this is arguably the best burger joint in the Atlanta area. It comes down to food quality and service. Every time I have had a burger here-from the tender beef on the sandwich that carries their name-to the lamb on the Cadillac burger-it’s always just as good as the first time. The texture, the amount of flavor, and the seasoning are all in proportion. Add this onto your must-go list of places in Google Maps right now! Haha

DON'T place take out orders at Moxie Burger Historic District. Poor customer service. They forgot about me on the phone. I waited for 10 minutes to place my order and they weren't even busy. I have been ordering from moxie burger, from the last 2 months. Today was the worst day.  I order a heater with a lettuce wraps, at the take out. Waited between 35- 45 minutes for it. Which is fine, but multiple people who order after me got their food. Including my coworkers. I got my order, with no sauce that came with the order. I waited another 5-7 min for a hot sauce and ranch, which wasn't a big deal. I felt I was forgotten again. The lady explain to me, the had to find the jalapeno ranch, that why it took so long. I like moxie so, I shook it off like it wasn't big deal. When I got the office, my suppose to be medium well was medium rare. I try to eat, but I couldn't because I don't eat medium rare food. Now I just wasted money and was late coming back to work. For a incorrect order. Anytime I come, I convinced coworkers to come here. Never again, I am so disappointed. Beautiful outdoor seating on the green.  Great casual spot for a relaxing meal.

This place is phenomenal. Bless the Saint who invented pickle chips. The burgers are, of course, delicious. The ambiance is odd, but not in a bad way, it sort of gave me the feeling I was eating my lunch in an oversized tree house. The view out over the Old Mill is gorgeous this time of year. The tables were clean, the staff friendly, I really have nothing but good things to say about this place. I definitely recommend it.

The food is great.  Strongly recommend getting the classic Moxie Burger.  Outside seating is nice.  Shady areas and spots In the sun.  It is quite exposed to nature though as a squirrel decided to join us for our meal.

We had high hopes for this burger restaurant prior to coming in but found an awkward setup with front ordering and delivery to your table rather than being waited on. The seating dining environment wasnt all that was awkward though: the line or direction to the cashier to order was un clear, there were no signs and the cashier didnt have a posted menu but pront outs on the counter. There was a bar on the other end of the restaurant and you had to buy your drinks you planned to have with the meal and then sit down with the drinks.  The food was also less than expected, with some interesting but poor executed twists. The salad I bought was way too sweet and had fried cheese balls that were also sweetened on the outside. My boyfriend's potato fries were seasoned with cinnamon and made slightly sweet. My brother and boyfriend also both said that the burger seemed to lack unique character. While the meal was filling, it was awkward having to get up to ask for a take out box when needed since we werent waited on. The enployees were all very young and immature, one saying "Thats what she said" when I made a comment about the meal being big when asking for a box. The prices are also higher than posted online. With other great burger places less than a mile away, (our favorite is Lucky's Burger and Brew) we wont be coming back here.
Cozy atmosphere, friendly and attentive staff

Consistently good food and service. The Chicago hotdog is my favorite dog. The Entrepreneur, naked w all the veges on the side, is how I roll on the burger. Fries are fantastic here. Great place to eat after a hike down by the old Roswell Mill.

The first two visits were excellent, but my third visit wasn’t what I expected. I talked with the manager, and he was wonderful. I felt completely assured that my concern would be resolved. We will definitely go back!  1. The menu is outstanding 2. The location is perfect 3. It’s kid-friendly, yet casual and nice enough to have a beer and watch a football game 4. I believe that the managers will be working with the staff to set the standard of service high  A revised review, Joanna Geeker

First timer today, Moxie is YUM-O. Super nice and friendly staff, I especially liked the no nonsense way to order and seat yourself. I ordered the Build Your Own with Black Angus Beef. I also loved that they have fresh instead of pickled jalapeños. I don’t live close to this place but if I have the chance to come again I definitely will. Great burger, great service.

EDIT:  I have eaten here a few times within the past month and the quality has gone WAY downhill. The final straw was when my girlfriend found a piece of tinfoil and a stem in the blue ribbon burger she ordered.  That's not a small error or an off night and cannot be excused.  I can't leave my 5 star rating up anymore and I won't be coming back.  My original review from 9 months ago.  Amazing burger place. OMG! FINALLY!! I found a place that appreciates zucchini fries. I searched high and low throughout the city for fried zucchini. Cheesecake Factory makes them way too thick. Thank u so much MB for getting this right.  I also had the onion strings. Both were fried perfectly and in fresh grease. Don’t act like you don’t go to places that have burnt looking and tasting fried foods because they keep reusing the grease!😳. I will be back to try the veggie burger.  This rating is solely on the zucchini fries and the onion rings!   This is really a friendly atmosphere. Cute outdoor patio nice bar and has WiFi. You can’t miss here!  Thank you Thank you🙌🏽

Literally the best hamburger I've had in my life. Best food. Best service. Best atmosphere and if you make it into a day in roswell you can go to the mill and swim then to moxie. Nothing else like a day like that

I may try this place again one day, but it's a little bit too expensive for the taste and to recommend to a friend.  Zucchini fries are awesome though! (one extra star for that) :D

I HATE leaving these types of reviews, but I feel this is only fair so management understands and local patrons can remain informed.  Unfortunately, I came down with food poisoning after eating here on April 18th, approx. 4 or 5pm.  I was visiting right before conducting a speaking event and this place was within walking distance. I ordered a side salad and fries, and left it at that. All other food I had eaten at home, including the previous day, and shared meals with my spouse, who wasn't sick.  This was the only possible place I could have pick food poisoning up, considering my other food and drink were from my own home. I was ill the following 2 days and felt really lucky that it was mild. However, it still cost me another speaking event, as I had to cancel. Who wants to listen to a speaker that has to interrupt themselves every 30 minutes to be sick? NO ONE.  My only guess is improper food safety. There weren't very many staff on hand when I went, and they were all extremely young.  My side salad came with overly warm ranch dressing... which I ignored like a ding-dong and didn't send back. The food itself tasted fine, but I think the near-hot ranch dressing was what did me in.  Please, work with your younger staff and inform them of dairy safety and food handling safety. You could really hurt someone who is elderly or immune-compromised. It only takes ONE unfortunately slip.  Best of luck, I hope this helps.

I should have just taken his burger from him! When we sent them back they ran off with his fried pickles.  They were really good so I scooped em all off the plate onto a napkin as they were whisked away back to the kitchen.  The cook took our burgers and threw them back on the grill.  My friend's still had his bite marks in it when it came back and the tomato had gone cold.  Mine was missing most of the cheese now and was somehow overcooked on the outside and still bloody in the middle.  I'm taking the time to write this review b/c I think its a great little bar and I'd like to be a regular as I live close by, but for a ($12?) sandwhich, I expect them to make a new one if the cook doesn't get it right the first time. Pretty pleasant place all the way around. It's a burger spot, mainly, that serves a healthy selection of beer and wine as well. All of the burgers are 6oz patties and start around $7.  Make your own and choose one of the defined recipes.  That burger price does not come with a side or drink so depending on what you get, you'll probably land in the $10-15 range. Respectable lunch, I guess.  When you walk in, grab a menu if you're not familiar with the system. You basically order at the counter and then go wait for your food at your table. The menu is pretty extensive which caused me to start mildly panicking as my turn to order was coming up. :-) I couldn't decide between the Moxie or the Heater.  I went with the Moxie. It sounded like the clutch, house burger that had to be tried for a first-time visit. Added some zucchini fries with that. It's one of a handful of places I know that serve zucchini fries -- one of the best things on earth -- so it couldn't be missed.  The Moxie comes with bacon, pimento cheese, and a fried green tomato. The tomato was dense and greasy. Layer that with bacon and the grease level skyrockets. The zucchini fries were also super greasy. Perhaps the fryer needs to be set the appropriate temperature. These were just saturated. Next time, Heater.  Overall, good flavor in everything. The interior is casual and relaxing. Staff is friendly.
